Kris Carpenter wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; The Internet Archive recently created a Heritrix Usage survey at:
&gt; 
&gt; http://www.surveymonkey.com/s.aspx?sm=wduuZtRuecv7PGkL6Cjo8Q_3d_3d 
&gt; &lt;http://www.surveymonkey.com/s.aspx?sm=wduuZtRuecv7PGkL6Cjo8Q_3d_3d&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; The goal of this survey is to document the breadth and depth of Heritrix
&gt; use cases to facilitate:
&gt; 
&gt; 1) Communication and collaboration within the user community
&gt; 2) Testing and verification of new software builds
&gt; 3) Prioritization of features and bug fixes
&gt; 4) Ongoing support of prior versions and migration paths to new builds
&gt; 5) More robust documentation of primary use cases and workflows.
&gt; 
&gt; This survey is designed to be filled out in its entirety per Heritrix
&gt; use case. If the person or persons responsible for crawling at your
&gt; institution do not have the time to fill this out more than once, please
&gt; have them provide details only for your primary use case.
&gt; 
&gt; The results of this survey will be made anonymous prior to distribution
&gt; to the community to encourage participation.
&gt; 
&gt; Thanks in advance for your help in this effort!
&gt; 
&gt; The Heritrix Engineering Team
&gt; 
